            <p>When you think of Terminal 4 as a bustling mini-city within JFK Airport, It is a vast, modern building that serves as a significant hub for <a href="https://www.faresmatch.com/delta-airlines-flights-reservations.aspx"><b>Delta Airlines</b></a> and many other international flag carriers. This terminal has been popular at the New York airport because it has many shops, restaurants, and lounges. Why is T4 essential? It is a primary gate for travellers flying to and from destinations all around the world, especially across Europe, Asia, and other continents. </p>
            <h2>Which Airlines Use Terminal 4 at JFK? </h2>
            <p>Terminal 4 is home to a long list of airlines, and the most significant player or major airline at Terminal 4 at New York Airport is Delta Airlines, which uses T4 for nearly all its flights. Other major airlines you'll find here include: </p>
