            <h3>How is Terminal 4 Laid Out (The "Map")?</h3>
            <p>There are two main areas for the gates of Terminal 4, and here are these –</p>
            <p>Concourse A – This concourse features gates A2 through A21, and it handles many international airlines, including Delta connection flights. </p>
            <p>Concourse B: It is among the larger concourses with gates B20 through B55, and Delta primarily uses it for both its domestic and international flights as well as by its SkyTeam partners. </p>
            <p>When we talk about connectivity, we can say that both concourses are connected to the main terminal building, where you'll find check-in, security, and arrivals. </p>
            <h2>What Can I Do at Terminal 4? (Shops, Food, Lounges) </h2>
            <p>Don't worry about the things to do at Terminal 4 JFK because you won't be bored or hungry at T4, and it offers a fantastic range of options. In terms of dining, you can visit Shake Shack and Dunkin to sit-down restaurants like the Palm Bar and Grille and Le Grand Comptoir (a wine bar). Many places are open 24 hours a day. When we talk about the shopping experience, there are excellent duty-free shops for cosmetics, liquor, and fashion. There are many airline lounges as well. Delta Sky Club is available in multiple locations in both Concourses A and B. Another lounge is the Virgin Atlanta Clubhouse. </p>
